A new date has been fixed by Justice Inyang Ekwo of the Federal High Court, sitting in Abuja to hear bail application filed by detained Deputy Commissioner of Police, Abba Kyari.  The court fixed February 28 for the hearing. Justice Ekwo fixed the date on Thursday, after counsel to the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency, Mike Kassa had informed the court that the bail application was not served on him. Kassa said though the applicant’s counsel served him with a motion on notice, he was yet to be served with the bail application. However, Kyari’s counsel, Cynthia Ikenna insisted before the court that there is a proof of service to that effect. Ikena prayed the court to confirm the proof of service in the court file. After going through the court file, Justice Ekwo directed the applicant’s lawyer, Ikenna to serve Kassa in open court. Meanwhile, the court has adjourned to February 28, to hear Abba Kyari’s bail application.  Source Cynthia Ikenna, the counsel to embattled former deputy commissioner of police (DCP), Abba Kyari, has prayed the court to grant him bail as he is hypertensive and Diabetic. Kyari who is in the NDLEA custody for his alleged involvement in drug trafficking had filed for his bail application which was… In "News" The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) has gotten an order to detain suspended Deputy Commissioner of Police, Abba Kyari for 14 days. The order was given by a Federal High Court in Abuja on Tuesday. The court granted permission to the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) to hold… In "News" A Federal High Court in Abuja, on Wednesday, fixed February 10 for the hearing of a suit seeking to stop the Nigeria Police Force and the Attorney-General of the Federation from arresting and extraditing a suspended Deputy Commissioner of Police, Abba Kyari. Justice Donatus Okorowo fixed the date following the… In "News"